<HR align="center" width="85%"><P>

 I'm just wondering about something that's been bothering me for a long time.  When or if will we see some retroactive changes made to the old world's 3d models? Good examples of things that scream for updating are:<P>
 
 The fact that 90% of the weapons in the Old World still use those terrible 12 triangle models, with the Longsword and Two Handed Sword meshes being most overused.  With so many good models used on so many useless weapons in Kunark, it seems a shame that most of the old world's equipment still uses meshes of such extreme low detail and quality that they aren't even up to par with the meshes used in Id software's original Quake(TM). An optional patch to upgrade some of these would be a welcome boon.  Certainly much less painful than watching weapons looted off high level mobs be only useful to newbies due to their terrible statistics but nice looks.<P>

 Why are so many of the sword-type meshes from Kunark designed like giant crossguard-less cake knives?  Even in a fantasy setting, most of these weapons look so cumbersome and unwieldy.<P>

 Why does the Iksar male attack-magic casting animation look so weak?  <P>
  
 If possible ( and desperately wanted by at least one patron(me)) can some of the additional detail that went into the creation of the Iksar player models be applied to  the old world player meshes?  As a 3d
vanimator myself its painful to see build/animation problems such as The monstrous gap under the chin of the dark elven heads visible when they are in robes. The texture stretching along the sides of trolls' guts. The way the armpit and shoulderblade triangles of Ogres stretch extremely far when they attack or scratch their crack.<P>

 The generally low resolution texturing applied to armors etc on the old world player races as opposed to the crisp detail on the iksar. The absence(sic) of variety in animation. all races melee attack the same way when using one handed weapons, run the same, idle the same ( look left, look right, put your arms down and pose)<P>
  
 That half elven leather looks absolutely horrible. That half elves cannot be any robe-wearing class! I want half elven monks and casters! (Talk to someone about this).<P>
  
 I'm sorry if this email is over-critical.<P>
 
 Brian Gardner

