<HR align="center" width="85%"><P>

 Hello,<P>

 I'm an avid gamer with a question about your job. What math do you use to genrate the shapes or geometry of the creatures in the game and what genrated computer programs are used?<P>
 
 Adam Hauck

<P> <P><b><i>
<font face="Georgia" size="4" color="#9F3215">
Milo Says:
</font></i></b><BR>

   Well, Adam, when we're building models, the computer does all of
the math!  That's part of what makes a great 3D modeling program:
having the computer do all the mundane work.  For my modeling, I use
Maya and 3D Studio MAX, as do just about all of Verant's artists and
world builders.  For textures, we use Adobe Photoshop, as well as
other paint programs and supplements like Painter and Bryce.<P>

